'''Argeus''' (Greek:  Ἀργαῖος, Argaios, Latin: Argaeus) was a Greek general who claimed the right to the throne of [[Macedonia (ancient kingdom)|ancient Macedon]] during the rule of [[Philip II of Macedon]].

Argeus was supported by [[Classical Athens|Athens]], which opposed Macedon, and used Athenian money to buy a mercenary army and take the port city of [[Methoni, Pieria|Methone]]. Argeus was ultimately not successful in opposing Philip, as Macedon was able to unite all of Greece by the time of Philip's death.

