{{Infobox person | name = Barbara Anna Kistler | native_name = | native_name_lang = | image = Barbara Kistler photo.jpg | image_size = 214px | alt = | caption = | birth_date = 21 October 1957 | birth_place = [[Zürich]], [[Switzerland]] | death_date = January 1993 | death_place = [[Tunceli Province]], [[Turkey]] | death_cause = | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = | nationality = [[Switzerland]] | education = | alma_mater = | occupation = politician, guerrilla | years_active = | employer = | organization = | agent = | known_for = [[Far-left politics|Far-left]] activism | notable_works = | style = | influences = | influenced = | party = [[Communist Party of Turkey/Marxist–Leninist]] | movement = Workers' and Peasants' Liberation Army of Turkey | opponents = | boards = | spouse = | partner = | children = | parents = | relatives = | website = | footnotes = | box_width = }}
'''Barbara Anna Kistler''' (21 November 1955 – January 1993) was a [[Swiss people|Swiss]] [[Maoism|maoist]] revolutionary, [[Communist Party of Turkey/Marxist–Leninist|TKP/ML]] activist and member of the Workers' and Peasants' Liberation Army of Turkey.
== Biography == Kistler was born in [[Zürich]], [[Switzerland]]. She was member of the Group Against Isolation (KGI),<ref>[http://www.sosyalistforum.net/olumsuzler/59290-alplerden-munzur'-enternasyonalizm-barbara-anna-kistler.html Sosyalist Forum - Barbara Anna Kistler] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131204001838/http://www.sosyalistforum.net/olumsuzler/59290-alplerden-munzur%27-enternasyonalizm-barbara-anna-kistler.html |date=December 4, 2013 }}</ref> which was seeking to build a Communist Party in Switzerland. In 1980, she met communists from [[Turkey]] who had fled to Switzerland to escape [[1980 Turkish coup d'état|the military coup]]. In 1986 Barbara Kistler came into contact with sympathizers of the TKP/ML.<ref>[http://www.babaerdogan.org/partizan/1993.html# Baba Erdogan: Anna KİSTLER]</ref> On 19 May 1991, she was arrested in [[Istanbul]] together with her comrades. She was held incommunicado for 10 days and according to Marcel Bosonnet (a Swiss lawyer) "severely tortured"<ref>.[https://www.amnesty.org/en/documents/eur44/071/1991/en/ Amnesty International: Barbara Kistler] </ref> Kistler was released on September 16 and returned to Switzerland. Then she went back to Turkey. She decided to go to the mountains of [[Turkey]] to join the armed struggle of the Workers' and Peasants' Liberation Army of Turkey. She was killed in [[Tunceli Province]], in 1993.<ref>[http://ch.indymedia.org/fr/2005/10/35787.shtml Barbara Kistler est née il y a 50 ans, le 21 octobre 1955]</ref><ref>[http://istanbul.indymedia.org/tr/news/2007/02/171450.php Barbara Anna Kistler] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203063813/http://istanbul.indymedia.org/tr/news/2007/02/171450.php |date=December 3, 2013 }}</ref>
