{{Economic systems sidebar |expanded=Transition}} '''Mutualization''' or '''mutualisation''' is the process by which a [[joint stock company]] changes legal form to a [[mutual organization]] or a [[cooperative]], so that the majority of the stock is [[Employee ownership|owned by employees]] or customers.<ref>[http://www.thefreedictionary.com/mutualization]. Dictionary.com</ref> [[Demutualization]] or [[privatization]] is the reverse process.
